        <p>Al-Hasakah is vital to Syria’s economy as a breadbasket: its fertile plains produce a large share of Syria’s wheat, barley, cotton, and lentils. It is also rich in oil and natural gas reserves, particularly around Rmeilan and Al-Suwaydiyah fields.</p>

